Shop UI flow (today: email+password, voucher/payment enrollment)
Screen 0: Landing / “Join as a Shop”

CTA: “Create shop account”

Secondary: “Sign in”

Screen 1: Shop registration (single form, one submit)

Purpose: collect everything once so you don’t revisit per feature.

Form sections:

Account

email

password

Shop profile

displayName

description (optional)

address (street, city, postalCode)

map pin / location (lat/lon)

Contact (shop contact, not owner identity)

contactPhoneE164 (required)

contactEmail (optional)

Billing / VAT

legalName

NIP

billing address (checkbox: “same as shop address”)

invoiceEmail (optional)

Terms

checkbox “I accept Terms” (+ optional termsVersion hidden)

(you set termsAcceptedAt server-side)

Submit calls: POST /api/enrollment/register

Result handling:

If response indicates PENDING_PAYMENT: navigate to Enrollment step.

If you ever allow “free active by default”, you’d go straight to dashboard.

Screen 2: Enrollment (choose how to activate)

Purpose: convert to ACTIVE so shop can act (quote/message).

Show status banner:

PENDING_PAYMENT → “Activate your shop to start receiving requests”

SUSPENDED → “Your shop is suspended — contact support”

ACTIVE → “Activated ✅”

Actions:

Voucher tab

input voucher code

button “Redeem”

calls POST /api/enrollment/voucher

Payment tab

button “Pay monthly”

calls POST /api/enrollment/payment

(today with stub: you can just “Confirm” immediately; later: Stripe Checkout)

After activation:

call GET /api/enrollment/status until ACTIVE (or just re-fetch once)

navigate to dashboard

UI routing rules (simple)

Unauthenticated: only /shop/register, /shop/login

Authenticated SHOP_USER:

if enrollment != ACTIVE → force /shop/enroll

else → allow /shop/* dashboard routes

Register: POST /api/enrollment/register

Login: your existing /api/auth/shops/signin

Status gate on every app load: GET /api/enrollment/status

Voucher: POST /api/enrollment/voucher


for changed contract look at auth-openapi.yml, enrollment-openapi.yml and shop-openapi.yml